<div class="mainpage-box" id="actions">
  <div class="tiers">
    <h3>How does CommonMorph work?</h3>
    <p>CommonMorph uses a three-step process where linguists and community members work together to
      develop resources for under-resourced languages.</p>
    <div class="tier">
      <div class="icon">1</div>
      <div>
        <h4>Expert Initialization</h4>
        <p>Linguists create empty morphological paradigms and assign morphosyntactic tags.
          They can import shared structures from related languages.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tier">
      <div class="icon">2</div>
      <div>
        <h4>Remote elicitation with AI Assistance</h4>
        <p>Community contributors provide the correct word forms with suggestions from AI models that improve with each
          submission.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tier">
      <div class="icon">3</div>
      <div>
        <h4>Community Validation</h4>
        <p>All data is reviewed collaboratively to ensure accuracyand cultural appropriateness.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="buttons">
      <a class="button" href="/tutorials">Explore the Platform</a>
      <a class="button" href="/user">Contribute!</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="mainpage-box">
  <div class="tiers">
    <h3>NLP-ready Datasets</h3>
